Absolutely — here’s a **ready-to-use master prompt** you can paste into ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Cursor, Bolt, Lovable, or any AI code generator to create your **full-stack AI services business platform**.

A couple of important notes first:

Use **email OTP**, not “Gmail OTP.” Gmail itself is not an auth provider for OTP; your app should send OTP to the user’s email address through an email service. For phone OTP, use a verification provider such as Twilio Verify. For subscription billing and 3/6/12-month plans, Stripe Billing is a strong fit. For a modern full-stack app, **Next.js App Router** is current and production-ready, and Stripe officially supports recurring subscription lifecycles. ([Next.js][1])

Also, Auth.js supports authentication patterns including email flows, but for **OTP by email + phone + activity tracking + admin dashboard + subscriptions**, a custom auth layer with database-backed verification is usually cleaner than relying only on a simple magic-link flow. Twilio Verify supports OTP verification workflows across channels including SMS and email. ([Auth.js][2])

